   "source": [
    "## ðŸ”‘ GitHub Config / Commit Recovery\n",
    "\n",
    "Check current config:\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "git config --list\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Fix username/email if wrong:\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "git config --global user.name \"your-username\"\n",
    "git config --global user.email \"your-email@example.com\"\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "directory-clone",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## ðŸ”‘ Directory + Clone Recovery\n",
    "\n",
    "Navigate into repo directory:\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "cd ~/your-username\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "If directory missing:\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "mkdir ~/your-username\n",
    "cd ~/your-username\n",
    "git clone https://github.com/your-username/repo.git\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "venv",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## ðŸ”‘ Virtual Environment Recovery\n",
    "\n",
    "Activate venv:\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "source venv/bin/activate\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "If not working:\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "./scripts/venv.sh\n",
    "source venv/bin/activate\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Open VS Code from project directory with venv active:\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "code .\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "vscode-memory",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## ðŸ”‘ VS Code Launch & Memory Fix\n",
    "\n",
    "- Ensure `(venv)` shows in terminal.\n",
    "- In Jupyter, select the Python kernel with `(venv)`.\n",
    "- If wrong projects keep opening:\n",
    "  - Shift+Cmd+P (Mac) or Shift+Ctrl+P (Windows/KASM)\n",
    "  - Type `Clear Recently Open`\n",
    "  - Close VS Code and reopen properly."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "version-checks",
